    "narrative": "**Gunnar Henderson** stands out as the clear cornerstone of today\u2019s lineup with an elite score of 81.88. Facing Houser, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive park factor boost (+16%) and a favorable platoon advantage, making him our highest-upside play for both R and HR production. **Marcell Ozuna** and **Miguel Vargas** also offer strong daily value; **Marcell Ozuna** is buoyed by a 10% wind-out factor at the stadium, while **Miguel Vargas** earns a 64.07 score due to an excellent leadoff spot and similar weather support. These players represent our best chances to rack up counting stats against favorable expected ERAs.\n\nManaging the roster in a 5x5 format requires constant attention to the marginal tier, where **Kyle Tucker** and **Andy Pages** are forced into difficult matchups against deGrom. Despite the elite nature of the opposing arm, **Kyle Tucker** remains a must-start due to his profile, whereas **Andy Pages** sees his efficiency dip to 47.63, narrowly keeping his spot despite the threat posed by deGrom\u2019s efficiency. Our most difficult bench decision involved **Josh Jung**, who posted a 55.14 score against Sasaki. While **Josh Jung** carries significant raw power, he was edged out by **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Jorge Polanco**, whose order positions and situational projections provided just enough of an efficiency buffer to justify their inclusion over the bench unit.\n\nWe are closely monitoring the 39% rain risk hanging over **Jackson Merrill** in his matchup against Freeland. While **Jackson Merrill** currently projects at 58.20, any further degradation in weather could render him a liability; if the game is delayed or postponed, we will be forced to pivot to our bench depth. Additionally, **Drake Baldwin** remains at a 59.84 projection, though his status as a \"Lineup Pending\" player means we must verify his spot in the order before first pitch to ensure he maintains the projected gains from the #2 hole. With the scarcity of SB a primary concern, the presence of **Heliot Ramos** and the rest of our active starters remains focused on maintaining category efficiency without over-extending our total game caps.",
